      "text": [
        " عَلَيَّ اَلْمَشْيُ إِلَى بَيْتِ اَللَّهِ اَلْحَرَامِ قَالَ \"إِذَا لَمْ يَقُلْ لِلَّهِ عَلَيَّ فَلَيْسَ بِشَيْءٍ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4278 - Imam (as) was asked about a man who, in a state of anger, said:\n\"Upon me is to walk to the Sacred House of Allah (swt).\"\nImam (as) said: \"If he did not say, 'It is a vow to Allah (swt) upon me,' then it is of no consequence.\""
        ]
      }
    },
